{
  "stem": "443.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the military needed, those days, hay for the horses, because all the Germans were pulling their-- their-- their cannons, and all the wagons was pulled by-- not even horses, they're called-- they're a mixture of a mule and a horse.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They're called mulesel.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's a horse that's stronger than a horse and stronger than a mule.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they-- it could even eat wood.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So the only way to-- for them to be able to do their jobs, we had to go up in the hills and uncover the snow and try to take the hay in bundles and bring it down to a place, to a area, where there was a train waiting.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When the train was full with hay, they used to take it away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Next day, there came another empty train.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were there, about 250 boys.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] And we were doing this from morning to night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So while the people were in the ghetto, we were up there doing this kind of work.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We didn't know what's going on at home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But it happened to be pace of time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was already in that place, and my mother sent with one of employees that helped work in the mikveh, he sent some money and send me some potato latkes.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Can you imagine receiving potato latkes in that place?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he had to smuggle in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It wasn't so easy for him to come, to look me up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But he gave me some pengos, he brought me some Hungarian money, and he brought me something to eat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's all-- and I asked the man what is going on at home, he said he didn't want to tell me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was afraid to tell us because we might rebel.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
